    • Uses of JavaWiget in com.k2.JavaFactory.impl

      Classes in com.k2.JavaFactory.impl that implement JavaWiget 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AnnotationWigetImpl
      This wiget includes an annotation in the assembled java code Annotations are written on their own line(s) by default but can be overriden by setting the parameter inline to true The annotation wiget does not end with a newline on the output to allow annotations to be inline if required
      class  ClassWigetImpl
      This wiget writes a java type of class The wiget does not include the package clause of the list of dependencies to allow the class wiget to be embedded in other wigets
      class  CompilationUnitWigetImpl
      The compilation unit wiget writes the package and imports clauses of a compilation unit before writing the wigets added to the compilation unit body.
      class  EnumValueWigetImpl
      This wiget output the java source code for an enumeration value This wiget should only be included within an enumeration wiget
      class  EnumWigetImpl
      This wiget writes a java type of enum The wiget does not include the package clause of the list of dependencies to allow the enum wiget to be embedded in other type wigets
      class  FieldWigetImpl
      This wiget writes fields of java class The java field wiget includes getters and setters, javadoc and annotations
      class  IntertfaceWigetImpl
      This wiget writes a java type of interface The wiget does not include the package clause of the list of dependencies to allow the interface wiget to be embedded in other wigets
      class  MethodSignatureWigetImpl
      Write the method signature The method signature wiget does not end with a new line, neither does it end with a ';' this allows the method signature wiget to be used to write the method signature of both interface method signatures and class method signatures
      class  MethodWigetImpl
      Write the java source for a method in a class
